I am building a full-stack digital paintings / museum-style web app.

Frontend:

React + TypeScript (Vite)
Chakra UI
Framer Motion (animations + page transitions)
React Router

Current frontend features:

Landing page with hero, animated geometric background, carousel, feature cards
Gallery page with:
4-column responsive grid (masonry-like via varying heights)
hover interactions (zoom, overlay, favorite button)
glassmorphism filter panel with active states
search bar (currently frontend-only filtering)
scroll reveal animations (Framer Motion)
Painting details page (dynamic route /painting/:id)
hero image
artist, year, medium
description/story
related paintings section
Navbar with navigation to Landing, Gallery, Login, Signup

Design style:

modern digital museum aesthetic
Apple-like UI polish
glassmorphism + soft lighting + subtle motion
minimal but premium feel

Current limitation:

All paintings are hardcoded in frontend arrays
No backend or database exists yet

Next step:
I want to build a real backend using:

Node.js
Express.js
MongoDB (Mongoose likely)

Backend goal:

Replace mock data with real API
Store paintings as structured objects:
id
title
artist
year
medium
story/description
image URLs
tags (for filtering)
related paintings (relationships between artworks)
Support fetching all paintings
Support fetching single painting by ID
Later expand to search/filter endpoints and possibly image upload system

Goal of architecture:
Make the app fully data-driven and scalable, turning it into a real museum-style platform instead of static frontend mocks.

